# Conditionals Outside JSX

You can't put an `if` statement directly inside JSX, but you can use it outside to decide what to return.

## Example

```jsx
function Greeting({ isLoggedIn }) {
  if (isLoggedIn) {
    return <h1>Welcome back!</h1>;
  } else {
    return <h1>Please sign in.</h1>;
  }
}
```

The component returns different JSX based on the condition. This is simple and readable for straightforward logic.

